definition.value: Xq27.3q28 duplication syndrome is a recently described syndrome characterized by short stature, hypogonadism, developmental delay and facial dysmorphism.

Kleefstra syndrome (KS) is a genetic disorder characterized by intellectual disability, childhood hypotonia, severe expressive speech delay and a distinctive facial appearance with a spectrum of additional clinical features.

Nakajo-Nishimura syndrome (NNS) is a rare autoinflammatory disorder belonging to the proteasome disability syndrome (see this term) group, and characterized by pernio-like lesions appearing in infancy followed by recurrent fever, nodular skin eruption, partial lipodystrophy (mainly in upper extremities and face) and joint contractures.

definition.value: Blepharophimosis - epicanthus inversus - ptosis (BPES) due to 3q23 microdeletion is a form of BPES (see this term), which in addition to the classical eyelids features of BPES, present genitourinary anomalies, spastic diplegia and speech delay.

label.value: Blepharophimosis - epicanthus inversus - ptosis due to a point mutation

definition.value: Blepharophimosis-epicanthus inversus-ptosis (BPES) due to a point mutation is a form of BPES (see this term), characterized by the classical eyelid malformation (blepharophimosis, ptosis, epicanthus inversus, and telecanthus) which may be accompanied by growth retardation and primary ovary failure.

label.value: obsolete_Blepharophimosis - epicanthus inversus - ptosis due to polyA expansion

definition.value: Blepharophimosis - epicanthus inversus - ptosis (BPES) due to polyA expansion is a form of BPES (see this term), characterized by the classical eyelid malformation (blepharophimosis, ptosis, epicanthus inversus, and telecanthus) which may be associated with a mild ovarian involvement.

definition.value: 3M syndrome is a primordial growth disorder characterized by low birth weight, reduced birth length, severe postnatal growth restriction, a spectrum of minor anomalies (including facial dysmorphism) and normal intelligence.
